  "title": "Logistics Officer (Shipping / Haulier)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Coordinate and manage shipping and logistics operations to ensure efficient, compliant, and timely movement of goods. Collaborate with internal teams and external partners to optimize shipment schedules and haulage activities, driving operational excellence in the freight forwarding industry.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Shipping Officer</p><ul><li>Coordinate and arrange daily import and export shipments to meet operational timelines</li><li>Prepare and verify shipping documents including invoices, packing lists, and customs declarations to ensure accuracy and compliance</li><li>Monitor and track shipments proactively to resolve logistical issues and ensure timely delivery</li><li>Communicate effectively with internal departments to align shipping schedules with business needs</li><li>Ensure adherence to shipping regulations, company policies, and customer requirements to maintain compliance</li></ul><p>Logistics Officer (Haulier)</p><ul><li>Plan and schedule container trucking and haulage activities utilizing the company’s internal fleet for optimal resource use</li><li>Liaise closely with drivers, port officers, and warehouse teams to coordinate timely collection and delivery of shipments</li><li>Monitor fleet movements and promptly resolve operational or delivery issues to maintain service reliability</li><li>Maintain accurate transport documentation and update shipment status in the system to support transparency</li><li>Support continuous improvement initiatives to enhance haulage efficiency and service quality</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></li><li>GCE 'O' Level or Diploma in Logistics, Supply Chain Management, or equivalent</li><li>At least 1–2 years of experience in shipping, logistics, or coordination roles</li></ul><p><br />Qualified or interested candidates, please submit your updated resume by using the Apply Now Button</p><p>We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates will be notified<br /><br />Lai Kah Wei</p><p>Registration Number: R25158317</p><p>EA License Number: 18C9027</p>",
